3. Pertinent Policies (The Handbook)

Pet Policy: Generally no pets except fish in aquarium. Service Animals/ESAs must be approved through Disability Support Services.

Guest Policy:
- Overnight Guests must be registered through online portal in Roompact.
- Limit: Guests may stay no more than 3 consecutive nights.
- Frequency: Maximum of 6 nights total per month.
- Escort Rule: Guests must be escorted by the host resident at all times (24/7) within the building.
- Consent: Roommate(s) must approve of the guest presence.
- Minors: Guests under 18 are generally prohibited unless immediate family (policy varies by hall/apartment context).

Alcohol & Drugs:
- Residence Halls: STRICTLY PROHIBITED regardless of age. Possession or consumption is a violation.
- Apartments: Alcohol not prohibited for students of legal drinking age.
- Paraphernalia: Beer bongs, kegs, and funnels are prohibited regardless of age.
- Empty Containers: Prohibited in Residence Halls.

Quiet Hours:
- Standard Hours:
   - Sunday - Thursday: 10:00 PM - 10:00 AM
   - Friday - Saturday: 12:00 AM (Midnight) - 10:00 AM
- Courtesy Hours: 24 hours a day. Noise should not be audible outside the room.
- Finals Week: 24-hour quiet hours are enforced.

Lockouts & Keys:
- ALL residence hall rooms and apartment units use physical keys for room/unit entry.
- Electronic door access (key card / student ID card) is used ONLY for exterior building entrance doors of residence halls.
- Losing a physical room key always requires a lock recore ($75) for security — a new key cannot simply be issued without recoring.
- Procedure: Visit Wilkerson Service Center (during open hours) or call RA or RM on Duty if locked out of room/apartment.
- Business Hours Fee: $10.00
- After Hours Fee: $25.00
- Lost Key (Recore): $75.00 charge to change the core (mandatory for security).

