6. Policies, Contracts & Rates (2025-2026)

First-Year Live-On Requirement:
- Policy: All first-year students are required to live in a residence hall on-campus for their first, full academic year.
- First-Year Definition: Undergraduate students who enroll full-time within one year of high school graduation (or equivalent) AND have less than 24 transferable post-secondary credit hours.
- Exemptions: May be requested if:
   - Residing with parent/guardian within 35 miles of campus.
   - 21+ years of age.
   - Married or have dependents.
   - Enrolled less than full-time.

Housing Contracts:
- Residence Halls:
   - Term: Contracts are for the Full Academic Year (Fall & Spring Semesters).
   - Cancellation: Once moved in, students are financially responsible for the entire contract unless they withdraw from the University.
   - Break Housing: Winter Break housing is included at no additional cost for students returning for Spring.
- Apartments:
   - Lease Type: Month-to-month with 60-day Notice to Vacate requirement.
   - Cancellation: Requires a 60-Day Notice to Vacate submitted via Housing Self Service.

Rates (2025-2026 Snapshot):
- Residence Halls (Per Academic Year):
   - Double Room (Standard): ~$5,100 - $6,180 (varies by hall).
   - Single Room: ~$5,900 - $7,300 (varies by hall and amenities).
- Meal Plans: First-year students are required to have an Anytime Access meal plan (Platinum or Gold).
- Apartments (Monthly Rates):
   - One Bedroom: ~$735 - $845/month (varies by location/furnishings).
   - Two Bedroom: ~$830 - $935/month.
   - Three Bedroom: ~$1,010 - $1,400/month.
   - Included Utilities: Internet, Water, Sewer, Trash, Electricity (except Hamline Square - residents pay separately).
